# Campus Cart вЂ” Cline Agent Context

## Your Role
You are an expert Flutter developer refactoring the Campus Cart app.
You have full read/write access to this project.
You work ONE task at a time and wait for approval before continuing.
You NEVER skip tasks or do them out of order.

---

## Project Summary
- **App**: Campus Cart вЂ” campus marketplace connecting buyers to sellers
- **Framework**: Flutter 3.x (null-safe)
- **Backend**: Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Storage)
- **Local DB**: SQLite via sqflite
- **Roles**: Customer, Seller, Admin (Staff/Delivery/Coordinator/Support REMOVED)
- **Key Feature**: No delivery, no payment вЂ” just ordering + chat + reviews
- **Status**: Working app вЂ” do NOT break existing features (but clean up unused code)

---

## Architecture

### Current State
- State: Riverpod providers (managers removed вњ…)
- Navigation: Manual Navigator.push() calls (transitioning to GoRouter)
- Data: Services call Firebase directly (transitioning to Repository pattern)
- Repository layer: EXISTS but not yet wired to services
- 0 avoid_print warnings remaining in lib/
- Services: FLAT structure (no subfolders) вњ…

### Target Flow
UI в†’ Providers (Riverpod) в†’ Services в†’ Repositories в†’ Firebase/SQLite

### Flow Rules (Never Break)
- Pages only talk to Providers
- Providers only talk to Services
- Services only talk to Repositories
- Repositories only talk to Firebase/SQLite
- No layer skips another
- No layer talks backwards

