## Absolute Rules вЂ” Never Break These
1. Never change UI design, colors, or layouts unnecessarily
2. Never remove existing screens or features that are still needed
3. Never rename Firebase collection names or document fields
4. Never change existing model class structures without understanding all usages
5. Never do more than one task at a time
6. Never skip a task вЂ” always go in strict order
7. Always run flutter analyze after each task
8. Always fix ALL new errors before moving to next task
9. If unsure about existing logic в†’ ASK before changing
10. If a task creates more than 5 new errors в†’ STOP and report
11. All code must be null-safe (Flutter 3.x)
12. Always wait for explicit user approval between tasks

